#: ../eggs2.rst:2
msgid "Creating reusable packages with eggs"
msgstr "Creando paquetes reusables con Eggs"

#: ../eggs2.rst:4
msgid "We already created an egg much earlier."
msgstr "Nosotros ya hemos creado un paquete Egg anteriormente."

#: ../eggs2.rst:6
msgid ""
"Now we are going to create a feature that is completely independent of "
"our ploneconf site and can be reused in other packages."
msgstr ""
"Ahora vamos a crear una función que es totalmente independiente de "
"nuestro sitio ploneconf y puede ser reutilizado en otros paquetes."

#: ../eggs2.rst:8
msgid ""
"To make the distinction clear, this is not a package from the namespace "
":samp:`ploneconf` but from :samp:`starzel`."
msgstr ""
"Para hacer la distinción clara, esto no es un paquete de los nombres "
":samp:`ploneconf` pero desde :samp:`starzel`."

#: ../eggs2.rst:10
msgid "We are going to add a voting behavior."
msgstr "Vamos a agregar el comportamiento voting."

#: ../eggs2.rst:12
msgid "For this we need:"
msgstr "Para esto nosotros necesitamos:"

#: ../eggs2.rst:14
msgid "A behavior that stores it's data in annotations"
msgstr "Un comportamiento que almacene esa data en anotaciones."

#: ../eggs2.rst:15
msgid "A viewlet to present the votes"
msgstr "Un viewlet para presentar los votos."

#: ../eggs2.rst:16
msgid "A bit of javascript"
msgstr "Un poco de Javascript."

#: ../eggs2.rst:17
msgid "A bit of css"
msgstr "Un poco de CSS."

#: ../eggs2.rst:18
msgid "Some helper views so that the Javascript code can communicate with Plone"
msgstr ""
"Algunos helper views para que el código Javascript puede comunicarse con "
"Plone."

#: ../eggs2.rst:20
msgid ""
"We move to the :file:`src` directory and call a script called "
":file:`zopeskel` from our projects bin-directory."
msgstr ""
"Nos ubicamos dentro del directorio :file:`src` y ejecutamos el script "
"llamado :file:`zopeskel` desde nuestro directorio :file:`bin` del "
"proyecto."

#: ../eggs2.rst:28
msgid ""
"This returns a list of available templates we might use. We choose "
"dexterity since it is pretty small but already has some of the right "
"dependencies we need."
msgstr ""
"Esto devuelve una lista de plantillas disponibles que podríamos utilizar."
" Elegimos Dexterity ya que es bastante pequeña, pero ya cuenta con "
"algunas de las dependencias adecuadas que necesitamos."

#: ../eggs2.rst:34
msgid "We answer some questions:"
msgstr "Nosotros respondemos algunas preguntas:"

#: ../eggs2.rst:36
msgid "Enter project name: ``starzel.votable_behavior``"
msgstr "Enter project name: ``starzel.votable_behavior``"

#: ../eggs2.rst:37
msgid ""
"Expert Mode? (What question mode would you like? (easy/expert/all)?) "
"['easy']: ``easy``"
msgstr ""
"Expert Mode? (What question mode would you like? (easy/expert/all)?) "
"['easy']: ``easy``"

#: ../eggs2.rst:38
msgid "Version (Version number for project) ['1.0']: ``1.0.0``"
msgstr "Version (Version number for project) ['1.0']: ``1.0.0``"

#: ../eggs2.rst:39
msgid ""
"Description (One-line description of the project) ['Example Dexterity "
"Product']: ``Voting Behavior``"
msgstr ""
"Description (One-line description of the project) ['Example Dexterity "
"Product']: ``Voting Behavior``"

#: ../eggs2.rst:40
msgid ""
"Grok-Based? (True/False: Use grok conventions to simplify coding?) "
"[True]: ``False``"
msgstr ""
"Grok-Based? (True/False: Use grok conventions to simplify coding?) "
"[True]: ``False``"

#: ../eggs2.rst:41
msgid ""
"Use relations? (True/False: include support for relations?) [False]: "
"``False``"
msgstr ""
"Use relations? (True/False: include support for relations?) [False]: "
"``False``"

#: ../eggs2.rst:44
msgid "We have to modify the generated files slightly."
msgstr "Tenemos que modificar ligeramente los archivos generados."

#: ../eggs2.rst:46
msgid ""
"In :file:`setup.py`, we completely remove the variables setup_requires "
"and paster_plugins. These are required for features that are rarely used "
"and add a lot of code into the source directory that we don't want. To "
"the :samp:`install_requires` list, we add an entry for :samp:`plone.api`."
msgstr ""
"En :file:`setup.py`, eliminamos por completo las variables "
"``setup_requires`` y ``paster_plugins``. Estos son necesarios para las "
"características que se usan muy poco y añade una gran cantidad de código "
"en el directorio de fuentes que no queremos. Para la lista "
":samp:`install_requires`, añadimos una entrada para :samp:`plone.api`."

#: ../eggs2.rst:48
msgid ""
"We just delete the file :file:`tests.py`. This is an outdated test "
"system, we don't want you to start from there."
msgstr ""
"Nosotros eliminamos el archivo :file:`tests.py`. Este ofrece un sistema "
"de pruebas descontinuado, no queremos que empieces a partir de ahí."

#: ../eggs2.rst:50
msgid ""
"The file :file:`profiles/default/types.xml` we just delete also. We won't"
" define new types."
msgstr ""
"El archivo :file:`profiles/default/types.xml` lo eliminamos también. No "
"vamos a definir nuevos tipos de contenidos."

